</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="19" pageNumber="108" type="notes">
<paragraph pageId="19" pageNumber="108">
<pageBreakToken pageId="19" pageNumber="108" start="start">Notes</pageBreakToken>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="19" pageNumber="108">
<taxonomicName class="Sordariomycetes" family="Melanconiellaceae" genus="Sheathospora" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Sheathospora cornuta" order="Diaporthales" pageId="19" pageNumber="108" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="cornuta">Sheathospora cornuta</taxonomicName>
is proposed here as a new combination for 
<taxonomicName class="Sordariomycetes" family="Melanconidaceae" genus="Melanconiella" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Melanconiella cornuta" order="Diaporthales" pageId="19" pageNumber="108" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="cornuta">Melanconiella cornuta</taxonomicName>
. It is the type and currently only species of 
<taxonomicName class="Sordariomycetes" family="Melanconiellaceae" genus="Sheathospora" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Sheathospora" order="Diaporthales" pageId="19" pageNumber="108" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="genus">Sheathospora</taxonomicName>
and so far known from 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Cornaceae" genus="Cornus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Cornus controversa" order="Cornales" pageId="19" pageNumber="108" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="controversa">Cornus controversa</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Juglandaceae" genus="Juglans" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Juglans regia" order="Fagales" pageId="19" pageNumber="108" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="regia">Juglans regia</taxonomicName>
in China. The sexual morph of this species is unknown and further collections are required to elucidate its life cycle.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
